Job Description
The Company:Our Client is a large international provider of project delivery and consulting services to the resources & energy sectors. They have a large presence in the Middle East and are currently experiencing a sustained period of growth.The Role:Our client is urgently seeking to recruit a high calibre Port Master Planner for their busy team. The successful applicant will have the following skillset.
• 10 to 20 year experience
• Experience with planning of small craft harbours to major port terminals
• Understanding of container, bulk and oil and gas terminals including productivity and capacity calculations
• Understanding of port operations
• Understanding of port material handling
• Ability to work independently
• Diverse experience with infrastructure works
• Middle East experience preferred
• Chartered or equivalent (or approaching) is preferred.
On offer is a highly competitive rate with one of the leading consulting companies of the world.Essential Skills / Qualifications:Degree qualified
Chartership preferred but not essential.For further information or to discuss any opportunities, please contact Declan Strain at Fircroft on +
